A powerful cyclone hit Bangladesh and India, prompting mass evacuations.
Officials fear severe damage to property and infrastructure.
The storm, reminiscent of past disasters, poses a significant threat.
The United States and Germany offer emergency relief aid.
The cyclone caused widespread devastation, leaving many homeless and in need of urgent assistance.
Efforts are underway to provide shelter, clean water, and medical aid to the affected population.
The international community, including the United Nations World Food Program, is mobilizing resources to support those impacted by the cyclone.
